race.comment: CLIMATE CONTROL (3) strips fitter at his third run in and will appreciate the fast tempo. Chased right to the line with the 58kg when a tenacious fourth over 1200m at Scone. Kept fresh and can finish over the top of these. BEYOND MY KEN (1) resumes without a trial. Never a chance from the outside gate when a battling twelfth over 1100m at Randwick in Highway class last August. Expected to carry the 62.5kg and take a hand in the finish. ROCK 'N' REIGN (4) stalked the speed when a game third over 1000m at this track with the 60kg. Doesn't have to improve much to finish in the money. KING SOLEIL (6) back from a six-month break. Lone victory came over this course and distance first-up and he gets the ideal setup today.
